4 Sec. 2. NRS 369.485 is hereby amended to read as follows:
5 369.485 1. The Legislature hereby declares:
6 (a) That it is a privilege to engage in the business of selling
7 intoxicating liquor at the wholesale or retail level in this state;
8 (b) That the Legislature finds it necessary to impose certain
9 restrictions on the exercise of such privilege; and
10 (c) That it is the policy of this state to preclude the acquisition or
11 control of any retail liquor store by a wholesale liquor dealer.
12 2. As used in this section, unless the context requires
13 otherwise:
14 (a) “Delinquent payment” means the failure of a retail liquor
15 store to make payment to a wholesale dealer for liquor on or before
16 the 15th day of the month following delivery by the wholesale
17 dealer.
18 (b) “Payment” means the full legal discharge of the debt by the
19 wholesale dealer’s receipt of cash or its equivalent, including
20 ordinary and recognized means for discharge of indebtedness
21 excepting notes, pledges or other promises to pay at a future date. A
22 postdated check, a check not promptly deposited for collection or a
23 check dishonored on presentation for payment does not constitute
24 payment.
25 (c) “Payment in cash” means the full legal discharge of the debt
26 by delivery of cash, money order, certified check or a cashier’s or
27 similar bank officer’s check.
28 3. A wholesale dealer shall not:
29 (a) Loan any money or other thing of value to a retail liquor
30 store.
31 (b) Invest money, directly or indirectly, including through a
32 subsidiary or agent, in a retail liquor store.
33 (c) Furnish or provide any premises, building, bar or equipment
34 to a retail liquor store.
35 (d) Participate, directly or indirectly, in the operation of the
36 business of a retail liquor store.
37 (e) Sell liquor to a retail liquor store except for payment on or
38 before delivery or on terms requiring payment by the retail liquor
39 store before or on the 10th day of the month following delivery of
40 such liquor to it by the wholesale dealer.
41 (f) Sell liquor to a retail liquor store which is delinquent in
42 payment to such wholesale dealer except for payment in cash on or
43 before delivery.
44 4. On the 15th day of the month following the delivery of
45 liquor and on the 15th day of each month thereafter, the wholesale
